Reasoning: The paper deals with complexity classification of constraint satisfaction problems in the propositional logic of graphs, which is a topic that falls under the scope of theoretical computer science. The use of universal-algebraic approach and structural Ramsey theory suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper's focus on solving graph problems using algorithms and computational tools suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
